fields.physical_description:
Carpet, Ensi

WARP: white wool; Z2S; 16 per inch (60 per dm).

WEFT: brown wool; Z-spun, unplied; 2 shoots after each row of knots; between 18-20 knots per inch (74-81 per dm).

PILE: wool and cotton; 6 colours: dark red, red, orange, dark blue, brown, white (cotton); asymmetrical knot open to the right and tied around 2 threads; between 144-160 knots per sq. inch (2220-2430 per sq. dm).

SIDE FINISH: web of 5 cords, the outer one is oversewn with dark blue and the inner are paired in blocks of blue and dark red wool.

END FINISH: Lower: cut, leaving 1 cm of plain weave with blue weft.  Upper: cut.  There is a braid sewn onto outer border, it has 6 paired wefts (3 red and 3 blue) which form 2 bands of alternating blocks.  There is a black cord along the upper edge.

DESIGN: Field: dark red ground divided into 4 parts by a horizontal panel and 2 upright arch-shaped panels.  The horizontal panel has 3 bands of crossed trefoils and each upright has a plant with 5 pairs of white flowers and a single flower in the arch.  Each upright is outlined by 3 pairs of white S-motifs.  The field has 4 rows of stylised tendrils; with a row of white X-motifs and bars at the top and above and below the central panel.

Main border: not at the bottom.  Dark red ground with 4 flowering plants which become, at the top, 9 short flowering plants.

Inner and innermost borders: dark red ground with angular meander enclosing dark blue vertical bars.  Vertical bars only at the top.

Outer border: brown ground with linked red crosses and between are pairs of white rectangles containing brown hooks.  This border, at the top of the elem, changes into a row and 2 half of quartered lozenges in dark red and orange and continues along the bottom.
Elem: dark brown ground with 2 bands of stylised plants with pendant blossoms in dark red and orange.  Above this is (1) a band with dark red ground with eleven similar but truncated plants in dark blue (2) a band with dark red ground with 9 dark blue rectangles (5 outlined in orange) containing 23 bands of 3 motifs, a reduced version of the tendrils in the field.  
Upper panel: below the border with linked red crosses, there is a band of 6 and 1/2 linked and horned white arches with coloured blocks of triangles and squares within and between.

Date catalogued 2.4.96
fields.dimensions: Length: 179 cm, Width: 146 cm maximum, Width: 143 cm minimum, Weight: 10 kg
fields.production_note:
Mentioned in "Turkoman Rugs in the V & A", by M. Franses and R. Pinner (intro. by Donald King).  Analysis by L. Pinner. Hali 1980, Vol. 2, No. 4, p. 302, 304, 315.

cf: A.A. Bogolynbov (1909) (Ill. 4) ident. of "Antique Pende Engsi...This old Namazlik..."  J.M.A. Thompson (ed. 1973) notes: "I wish to underline that it was bought in a Saryk village of the Pende oasis, that it was used as an Engsi... this is clearly Saryk work...."  also illus. by Elena Tzareva (1984) (pl. 17) and identified as "Saryk ensi, 129th century", S.
Ulrich Schurmann (1969) (pl. 37) ident. "Kizil Ayak from Pendeh, Engsi or Namaslik, middle of the 19th century".  S
